-analyzing your own character, the sanctioned path would be Blizzard's Game Data API (§1.2) — but
-as noted, those endpoints do not currently exist.
+- `GET https://planners.maxroll.gg/profiles/load?profileId=<id>` — returns the full planner
+  payload (all variants / tabs) as JSON.
+- `GET https://assets-ng.maxroll.gg/d4planner/data.min.json` — game-data mapping file that
+  translates Maxroll's internal numeric nids to datamine `bnetFileName` values, which are the
+  join key against our catalog.
+
+Both endpoints are observable via browser devtools and are used by the importer. Endpoint bases
+can be overridden via `MAXROLL_PLANNER_API_BASE` and `MAXROLL_DATA_BASE` environment variables
+for testing.
+
+**Join key:** `bnetFileName` — a datamine-derived file identifier present on every affix, aspect,
+unique, skill, paragon board, and paragon glyph entry in our catalog. The importer performs
+exact-match lookups only; no label-match or tag-based fallbacks.
+
+**Cache:** `data.min.json` is cached to `DATA_DIR/maxroll-cache/data.min.<patch>.json` keyed by
+patch version. No TTL beyond patch-version invalidation.
+
+**ToS posture:** Maxroll's Terms of Service prohibit automated scraping. Fetching a single
+user-pasted planner URL for personal build analysis is the community-accepted "gray area" pattern
+(see `docs/future-import-paths.md` Path A). The importer never issues bulk or automated requests.
+Consistent with the posture documented in Path A and shared by tools like Diablo4Companion
+(289 stars, same API).
 
